{% macro ec_full(contract) -%}
## The five-stage audit gauntlet (verbatim)

This is the bar your work will be graded against. Every claim you make
about your work — every subtask declaration, every doer self-audit,
every checker verdict — should map back onto these stage cards. The
audit is the truth-of-record; everything upstream of it that contradicts
the bar will surface as a failed cycle.

The standards stage and architecture stage are PARALLEL but DISTINCT:

* `standards_referenced` cites only standards profile docs (under
  `standards_profiles_dir`). Language/framework "how to build it" rules.
* `architecture_referenced` cites only project-architecture docs (under
  `architecture_docs_dir`). This project's subsystem boundaries and
  contracts.

Validators reject wrong-bucket placement with a re-prompt; mis-routing
on retry-2 BLOCKs the plan.

